<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF8014463A5F52F91098DE4" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF8014463A5F52F91098DE4" blockId="26.[151,760,1327,1734]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463A5F52F926B8E64" bold="true" box="[151,282,1327,1350]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF801446216F52F91718E64" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[292,512,1327,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF801446216F52F91718E64" box="[292,512,1327,1350]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Platyxantha robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was completely overlooked by all subsequent authors and thus missing in all catalogues and publications. I have found two 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF8014461A8F56F91868EA4" box="[666,759,1391,1414]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntypes</typeStatus>
(male and an unsexed specimen) (
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFF8014462CEF58F91228E84" box="[508,595,1423,1446]" captionStart="Figs 105–112" captionStartId="24.[151,188,1945,1964]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,333,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[180,1408,333,1921]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 105–112. Habitus of species excluded from Taumacera. 105 – Fleutiauxia chinensis (Maulik, 1933) (male, syntype); 106 – F. chinensis (female, syntype of F. mutifrons Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963); 107 – Hoplosaenidea abdominalis (Jacoby, 1884) (male, holotype of Platyxantha wallacei Jacoby, 1895); 108 – Hoplosaenidea dohertyi (Jacoby, 1894) (female, syntype); 109 – Hyphaenia balyi (Jacoby, 1895) (female, lectotype); 110 – Pseudoscelida nigrolimbata (Jacoby, 1899) (male, syntype); 111 – Metrioidea grandis (Allard, 1889) (male, syntype of Platyxantha robusta Jacoby, 1895); 112 – Theopella bodjoensis (Duvivier, 1885) (female, syntype of Platyxantha quadraticollis Jacoby, 1896)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505542/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Fig. 111</figureCitation>
) in the BMNH. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014463A5F5AF921D8EE4" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,364,1455,1478]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463A5F5AF921D8EE4" box="[151,364,1455,1478]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Platyxantha robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is cospecific with 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF801446119F5AF925A8EC4" authority="(Allard, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Allard" baseAuthorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metrioidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF801446119F5AF91868EE4" box="[555,759,1455,1478]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Metrioidea grandis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014463ACF5CF92558EC4" author="ALLARD E." box="[158,292,1487,1510]" firstAuthor="Allard" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin ou Comptes-Rendus des Seances de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="lxvi-lxxxiii" part="1889" refId="ref30146" refString="ALLARD E. 1889 a: Note sur les galerucides, coleopteres phytophages. Bulletin ou Comptes-Rendus des Seances de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique 1889: lxvi-lxxxiii." title="Note sur les galerucides, coleopteres phytophages" type="journal volume" year="1889">Allard, 1889</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the new synonymy is proposed. Another species, 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014463C0F5EF91B78D24" authority="Mohamedsaid, 1997" authorityName="Mohamedsaid" authorityYear="1997" box="[242,710,1519,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metrioidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463C0F5EF92948D24" box="[242,485,1519,1542]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Metrioidea borneensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014462DEF5EF91B78D24" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." box="[492,710,1519,1542]" firstAuthor="Mohamedsaid" journalOrPublisher="Serangga" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="53 - 64" part="2" refId="ref32662" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 1997 a: The Malaysian species of the genus Palpoxena Baly (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Serangga 2: 53 - 64." title="The Malaysian species of the genus Palpoxena Baly (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1997">Mohamedsaid, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was already synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF80144629DF60F91318D04" authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1889" box="[431,576,1551,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Atysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF80144629DF60F91318D04" box="[431,576,1551,1574]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Atysa grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF801446156F60F93928D64" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." bookContentInfo="239 pp." firstAuthor="MOHAMEDSAID" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia-Moscow" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" refId="ref32942" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 2004: Catalogue of the Malaysian Chrysomelidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). Pensoft, Sofia-Moscow, 239 pp." title="Catalogue of the Malaysian Chrysomelidae (Insecta: Coleoptera)" type="book" year="2004">MOHAMEDSAID (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014463C3F62F92A38D64" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[241,466,1583,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463C3F62F92A38D64" box="[241,466,1583,1606]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Platyxantha robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from New 
<collectingCountry id="FCF01FD8FFF8014463A5F64F93958D44" box="[151,228,1615,1638]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Guinea</collectingCountry>
which must be an error as 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF80144613CF64F91AC8D44" baseAuthorityName="Allard" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[526,733,1615,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metrioidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF80144613CF64F91AC8D44" box="[526,733,1615,1638]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Metrioidea grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from Borneo. This is supported also by the existence of another possible male 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF80144612AF68F911A8D84" box="[536,619,1679,1702]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntype</typeStatus>
deposited in the MCZ with the locality label of “Borneo”.
</paragraph>
